        <br>
        <p><h4>Development of Network Intrusion Detection System (NIDS), with Machine Learning and Deep Learning, Recurrent Neural Network models, MERN web I/O System.</h4></p>
        <br>
        <p style="color: #fff;">Large numbers of businesses were affected by data infringes and Cyber -attacks due to dependency on the internet. To prevent such malicious activity, the network requires a system that detects anomalies and informs the user with alerts.</p>
        <p style="color: #fff;">This project detects Network Intrusion anomalies by using the NSL-KDD dataset. The deep learning model Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM), a superior version of RNN (Recurrent Neural Network), and KNN (K-Nearest Neighbors) method are used for binary and multi-class classification.</p>
        <p style="color: #fff;">The user enters the hacking parameters in the front end, which is designed using ReactJS. The model predicts the type of attack and provides information to the user. MongoDB is used for storing data, and NodeJS serves as the backend framework.</p>
        <p style="color: #fff;">The project is fully responsive and based on session and cookies concepts. Once the user is authenticated and logged in, it will not ask for login credentials on subsequent visits. The system only requests credentials when the user clicks the logout button. Google OAuth 2.0 is used for user authentication, and user details are stored as salted hashes in MongoDB.</p>
